Viber’s new CEO aims to take on WhatsApp with a new version of the messaging app, set to launch in March. Djamel Agaoua said the new version of Viber will function “more like a platform than a single-purpose app”, according to a report by Bloomberg. New features coming to the app include e-commerce and banking. “Users will be able to open a chat window with friends, look at restaurants, decide where to go, and make a reservation – all without exiting Viber,” stated the report. Payment through the app is alo planned. Agaoua said his goals with Viber are to: